ysis. These find-\nings provide valuable information, reinforcing the suitability of deep autoencoders for\nrobust hyperspectral image classification, thus significantly contributing to advances in\nremote sensing methodologies and practical applications in environmental monitoring,\nprecision agriculture, and urban planning.', 'language': None, 'chunk_index': 8}, {'score': 0.8519121, 'chunk_id': '67e9193a-bd1c-4afd-a671-bbb6eb77c73a_22', 'doc_id': '67e9193a-bd1c-4afd-a671-bbb6eb77c73a', 'content': '4\n\n---\n\n***Table 1**: Comparison of Autoencoder-based Techniques for Hyper-\nspectral Image Classification*', 'language': None, 'chunk_index': 22}]
